hearing about students in the uk celebrating graduation / golden jubilee while those in my home country continue suffering poverty and tyranny. I wish they had my life and I had theirs. I feel like we are all living in fighting each other. I wish they knew they had the life with British nationality almost middle class while those living in eveil dictatorship corruptans country. I feel life could be so much easier if we all lived somewhere else else with other people, I wish this world was fair and I knew my life would be better if I had British nationality getting hooked on drugs , parties house alcohol, sex while living in Chad both unemployment, dictatorship and more. I don't think poverty would exist, if only.......wow....

One of my friends once said about life " what if we knew how things would end would we still do it? " I think that's what. And I hope we will never get a clue after death.

Grady he is the nicest chadese immigrant in United Kingdom

He has been living in Brighton, UK for 6 years in a small cottage in good area, residence's have water rates, gas electricity and other service of the house are paid and estate agency helps look after flat on his behalf, landlord rent out spare room when sought, Grady pays £500 per month as students loan money out , previous tenants wanted to share two-bedroom flat with him but he was upset - worried of how they could act in his front room.
